,(subsection :title [Guild Artisan][
,(index "Guild Artisan")
,(subsubsection :title [Proficiencies][
   ,(itemize (item [Tool Proficiency: The tools required by your chosen guild])
             (item [Skill Proficiency: History or Streewise]))
    Starting Equipment:
    ,(itemize (item [Traditional clothes of your profression])
             (item [A ring with the seal of your guild])
             (item [The tools required to work as an artisan, possibly at a small local workshop]))
])

,(subsubsection :title [Feature: Guild Member][
    You are a registered member of your guild. 
    You have permission to practice your craft and take on an apprentive even in the restrictive feudal society.
    The guild will offer legal assistance in case you are ever accused of a crime.
])
,(enumeration [Guild]
        [Blacksmiths Guild - specializes in metalworking, including weapons, armor, and tools.]
        [Stonemasons Guild - works with stone to create buildings, monuments, and sculptures.]
        [Carpenter's Guild - focuses on woodworking, including building furniture, homes, and ships.]
        [Weavers Guild - creates textiles, including cloth, tapestries, and rugs.]
        [Glassblowers Guild - works with glass to create decorative objects, mirrors, and lenses.]
        [Embroiderers Guild - creates intricate embroidered designs on clothing and other textiles.]
        [Tanners Guild - works with animal hides and leather to create clothing, footwear, and other products.]
        [Brewers Guild - creates beer, ale, and other alcoholic beverages.]
        [Jewelers Guild - designs and creates jewelry using precious metals and gemstones.]
        [ Potters Guild - creates pottery, including dishes, vases, and other decorative objects.]
        [Calligraphers Guild - creates artistic writing, including scrolls, certificates, and invitations.]
        [ Perfumers Guild - creates perfumes and other scented products.])

,(enumeration [Adventuring]
        [Wanderlust: The artisan has a burning desire to explore the world and discover new cultures and traditions, which cannot be fulfilled within the confines of their guild.]
        [Accusation: The artisan has been accused of a crime they did not commit, and must flee the city to avoid arrest and clear their name.]
        [Rebellion: The artisan has become disillusioned with the corrupt and oppressive ruling class, and has joined a rebellion or resistance movement to fight for a better world.]
        [Corruption: The artisan's guild has been infiltrated by a corrupt official who demands bribes and favors in exchange for contracts and opportunities.]
        [Creativity: The guild's strict rules and regulations prevent the artisan from pursuing new and innovative techniques or materials, stifling their creativity.]
        [Debt: The artisan has fallen into debt due to unexpected expenses or a failed investment, and is being threatened by loan sharks or other unsavory characters.])

])

